    "Title": "Highly Dangerous Ambush",
    "TitleKey": "Eckhart_ShipAmbush_S_title",
    "Description": "ECKHART SECURITY, LLC.\nCONTRACTS & DISPATCH\n\nCONTRACT TYPE: Ship Ambush\nAPPROVAL CODE = ~mission(ApprovalCode)\n\nFOR IMMEDIATE PROCESSING\n\nRecently, we sent a contractor after a <EM4>~mission(AmbushTarget)</EM4>, who was leading a crew targeting the operations of an extremely important client. Unfortunately, it was a trap and we lost some good people. We can\u2019t let the target get away again, so we\u2019ve decided the best course of action is to give them a dose of their own medicine.  \n\nAmbushing this target seems like the safest course of action, and we\u2019ve identified a good spot for such an attack. There\u2019s an <EM4>emission cloud</EM4> near <EM4>~mission(Location|Address)</EM4> that the target and their crew frequently fly by. You can power down your ship and hide there until you\u2019re ready to strike. This crew is ruthless and extremely skilled. Don\u2019t make the same mistake as the previous contractor and go this alone. It would be best for you to bring a few trusted friends to help handle this crew.    \n\nPayment will be issued upon successful completion of contract. Plus, we\u2019ll throw in a bonus payment of <EM4>~mission(ScripAmount) MG Scrip</EM4> for the main contractor for taking care of this.\n\nThis contract is non-negotiable.\n\nThis message may contain confidential, proprietary, privileged and/or private information. The information is intended to be for the use of the individual or entity designated above.",
    "DescriptionKey": "Eckhart_ShipAmbush_S_desc",
    "DisplayDescription": "ECKHART SECURITY, LLC.\nCONTRACTS & DISPATCH\n\nCONTRACT TYPE: Ship Ambush\nAPPROVAL CODE = [ApprovalCode]\n\nFOR IMMEDIATE PROCESSING\n\nRecently, we sent a contractor after a <EM4>[AmbushTarget]</EM4>, who was leading a crew targeting the operations of an extremely important client. Unfortunately, it was a trap and we lost some good people. We can\u2019t let the target get away again, so we\u2019ve decided the best course of action is to give them a dose of their own medicine.  \n\nAmbushing this target seems like the safest course of action, and we\u2019ve identified a good spot for such an attack. There\u2019s an <EM4>emission cloud</EM4> near <EM4>Asteroid Mining Base</EM4> that the target and their crew frequently fly by. You can power down your ship and hide there until you\u2019re ready to strike. This crew is ruthless and extremely skilled. Don\u2019t make the same mistake as the previous contractor and go this alone. It would be best for you to bring a few trusted friends to help handle this crew.    \n\nPayment will be issued upon successful completion of contract. Plus, we\u2019ll throw in a bonus payment of <EM4>[ScripAmount] MG Scrip</EM4> for the main contractor for taking care of this.\n\nThis contract is non-negotiable.\n\nThis message may contain confidential, proprietary, privileged and/or private information. The information is intended to be for the use of the individual or entity designated above.",
